<i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLeopard-Fox-Tariq-Ali%2Fdp%2F1905422296%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1193166242%26sr%3D1-5&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">The Leopard and the Fox</a> </i>is Tariq's play about the overthrow and execution of Zulfikar Ali Bhutto, Pakistan's first prime minister--it was commissioned by the BBC, but the production was cancelled under pressure from Britain's Foreign Office.
